title: vaccineff
text: cohort design VE estimated using Hazard Ratios (\(HR\)) vaccinated unvaccinated populations according following equation: \[VE = (1-HR(t))\times100\] HR estimated using Cox Proportional Hazards model: \[h_g(t,s)=h_{0,g}\exp(\beta s)\] hazards modeled terms status vaccination. proportional hazards hypothesis checked using Schoenfeld test. hypothesis satisfied, recommended stratify population smaller groups (g) using confounding variables.

what: vaccineff: An R package with tools for estimating vaccine effectiveness and vaccine related metrics
title: Estimate Vaccine Effectiveness Based on Different Study Designs
text: vaccineff R package offers tools estimating vaccine effectiveness, using series epidemiological designs including cohort studies, test-negative case-control, screening methods (Torvaldsen McIntyre 2020). package provides set features preparing data, analyze different study designs assessing performance models. vaccineff developed Pontificia Universidad Javeriana part Epiverse-TRACE initiative.

what: Function to construct the inmunization date — get_immunization_date
title: Function to construct the inmunization date — get_immunization_date
text: function returns column immunization date corresponds analyzed outcome. register presents outcome, function search closest vaccine date outcome satisfies condition: vacc_date_col <= outcome_date_col - delay_time - immunization_delay. condition allows discriminate vaccine dates terms characteristic times days (delay_time)  associated outcome, onset symptoms reference event, characteristic time days patient considered immune (immunization_delay). parameters can set zero user without affecting results. register present outcome, immunization date can construct using closest vaccine date end study (take_first = FALSE), first vaccination date found (take_first = TRUE). Notice function works one several vaccines. case several vaccines, parameter outcome_date_col must passed vector (see example)

what: Assign outcome status or vaccination status — set_status
title: Assign outcome status or vaccination status — set_status
text: function generates binary status column using set columns, passed variable col_names. column must contain information outcomes vaccine dates. generates logical condition using operators & |, evaluates registers columns contain information. logical operator &, function returns success, columns contain information. hand, logical operator |, enough find one column information indicating success. recommended use method working several outcomes several vaccine doses. default, returns binary column 0 means outcome vaccine 1 means opposite. However, can also receive personalized options, e.g. c("v", "u") vaccinated unvaccinated.

title: Assign outcome status or vaccination status — set_status
code: set_status(data, col_names, operator = c("&", "|"), status = c(1, 0))

title: Assign outcome status or vaccination status — set_status
text: data Dataset, data.frame least one column generate status specified status. col_names Name names column(s) string character vector containing information status calculated. operator single logical operator evaluate condition. status two-element vector specifying values assigned indicate whether individual vaccinated e.g. c("v","u"). first element vector must status condition satisfied, .e., vaccinated, second element value indicating individual vaccinated.
